        <para id="id17660028">_____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id15902904">_____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id17147081">_____________________________________________________________________</para>
        <para id="id3662557">2. Where does energy come from?</para>
        <para id="id17177796">We obtain almost all energy indirectly from the sun. The sun radiates heat and light and still retains enough nuclear power to continue shining for the next 5 000 million years.</para>
        <figure id="id16458193">
          <media id="id16458193_media" alt="">
            <image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/graphics1-bd5a.png" id="id16458193__onlineimage" height="282" width="517"/>
          </media>
        </figure>
        <para id="id12514749">A bus or a train uses <emphasis effect="bold">fuel</emphasis> to transport passengers from one point to another in the same way that a person uses the sun as a source of energy.</para>
        <para id="id12864657"><emphasis effect="bold">Fuel</emphasis> is the substance in which energy is contained.</para>
